# Documentation Standards

## Consistency
- Keep README.md and REQUIREMENTS.md and DEVELOPMENT.md in sync with implementation
- Update documentation when making significant changes
- Ensure examples and code snippets remain accurate

## Structure
- Use clear TL;DR sections for quick reference
- Document production-ready status and key insights
- Include setup instructions and prerequisites

## Content Guidelines
- Document architectural decisions and rationale
- Include key insights discovered during development
- Provide practical examples and usage patterns
- Explain complex concepts with clear examples

## Maintenance
- Review documentation during code reviews
- Update version numbers and compatibility information
- Keep dependency lists current
- Remove outdated information promptly
